From e471306821b7193930fbecf93c511d1ea91405a0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reap-loop <dev@reap-loop.local>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 12:05:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pace: 0026 demand-driven admission (DS4_PACE_ADMIT) - CUSUM
 per-expert, constant-K targeted exchange

ANCHORED TO LOCAL LIVE-TREE 2026-07-10 (post-0018 /root/ds4/ds4.c, md5
771a39a861e9512fed2fc4528780e080; applies after 0020-pace-s1-slope-trigger
and 0021-pace-rotate-delta-prefetch). Requires 0020+0021; rebase needed
after pace-series canonization (the filed 0015/0016/0018 do not apply on a
clean base, see patches/README.md "Stato apply").

Demand-driven admission is a K-CONSTANT targeted exchange: a PRUNED (out-of-
mask) expert whose blocked demand is strong and persistent is ADMITTED by
evicting the least-used keep. It is qualitatively different from the wholesale
rotate (0015/0021) already refuted live (E-CAL: static >> rotate at equal
coverage, pod collapse ~gen126); here the warmup mask stays the anchor except
for justified, per-layer, one-in/one-out swaps. Never K0, never wholesale
re-ranking. Off by default; alternative to ROTATE (run with DS4_PACE_ROTATE=0).

Reuses the 0020 per-expert rmass (non-biased router_probs, decay =
DS4_PACE_ROTATE_DECAY, default 0.98) as the eviction EWMA - no new sensor. Per
(layer, pruned expert) it runs a CUSUM on the per-token requested share
S <- max(0, S + share - k_drift) with an excursion-length counter; on
S >= h with persistence >= p the expert is admitted, the least-rmass keep in
that layer (past its cooldown) is evicted, and only the ENTERED expert is paged
in via the 0021 delta-prefetch (~6.75 MiB, no full WRAP). An anti-thrash
cooldown protects the neo-admitted from eviction for N tokens; an optional
per-100-tok rate cap bounds churn. The trigger test and physical swap run once
per decode token in ds4_pace_tick (in PACE_HOLD, when no breath is due); the
layer hook only accumulates the CUSUM. Wholesale mask rebuilds (breath/rotate/
tighten) and prefill reset clear the CUSUM/cooldown state.

Env (defaults = E-ADMIT sim recommended config C, run
runs/ds4/20260710_eadmit_demand_admission, verdict positive):
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT=0            master switch (off)
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT_H=1.2        CUSUM admission threshold
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT_KDRIFT=0.02  per-token CUSUM drift (leak)
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT_PERSIST=2    min excursion length (tokens)
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT_COOLDOWN=16  neo-admitted not evictable for N tok
  DS4_PACE_ADMIT_MAX_PER_100=0  optional per-100-tok rate cap (0=off)

Provenance: sim recovers 13.7 pt of the late coverage FROZEN loses (0.485 ->
0.622; rotate32 0.662) at 5.4x less churn and ~zero rebounds; params stable
across traces (median regret 3.4 pt). Structural-boundary boost (variant D) is
deferred to v2 (needs a live boundary detector). Quality is NOT deducible from
the sane-trajectory sim (limit 1): gated on the live A/B S3.

JSONL: ev "admit" with layer, expert, evicted, cusum, keep; the reused 0021
delta-prefetch also emits "rotate_delta" (entered/exited/bytes) per swap batch.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
